      "explanation": "Real-time threads (SCHED_FIFO, SCHED_RR on Linux) have fixed priorities and preempt lower-priority threads immediately. Audio threads use this to avoid buffer underruns. Danger: a real-time thread that never yields can freeze the entire system."
